### Description

When a method is implemented using yield statements, an enumerator is automatically created. This enumerator type implements IAsyncEnumerator<T>. However, when attempting to access the MoveNextAsync() method through reflection, I encounter difficulty retrieving method information from the public method collection due to its implementation as a private method.

This is a blocker because I don't want to expose private methods in scripting engine through reflection.

### Reproduction Steps

```cs
public class TestAsyncYield
{
    public static async IAsyncEnumerator<int> GetEnumerator()
    {
        yield return 3;
        await Task.Delay(1000);
        yield return 1;
        await Task.Delay(1000);
        yield return 2;
        await Task.Delay(1000);
        yield return 3;
        await Task.Delay(1000);
        yield return 3;
    }
}

var type = TestAsyncYield.GetEnumerator().GetType();
//  The following method should return public interface method, but it doesn't
type.GetMethod("MoveNextAsync", BindingFlags.Public | BindingFlags.Instance);
```

### Expected behavior

```cs
var type = TestAsyncYield.GetEnumerator().GetType();
//  The following method should return public interface method info, but it doesn't
type.GetMethod("MoveNextAsync", BindingFlags.Public | BindingFlags.Instance);
```

### Actual behavior

The MoveNextAsync method is implemented privately.

